	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 727, footnote 31" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2115> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2115" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Colonized Croton (Liv. 34.45.3-5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1952> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1952" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "All served under Purpurio in Gaul (Liv. 31.21.8). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1948> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1948" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Though the names of these Legates are doubted by Münzer (RE) because the details of the accounts are drawn from annalistic sources, some are indubitably historical (e. g. Laetorius, and Valerius), and all should be listed." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1791> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1791" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Sempronius with troops and ships to try to break off the Aetolian peace with Philip of Macedon (Liv. 29.12.5). See above, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1790> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1790" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Only the nomen Laetorius is given in the text of Livy. C. is the praenomen of the Praetor of 210." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1672> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1672" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 27.8.4. C. Laetorius succeeded Q. Mucius Scaevola." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1602> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1602" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He appears at the beginning of the next year as Propraetor in Gaul (27.7.11; see note 1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1601> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1601" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Weissenborn notes that the army under Laetorius at Ariminum (Liv. 27.7.11) consisted of the two legions which according to 26.28.4-5 were to be sent to Gaul under an appointee of the Consul. Perhaps L. was first Pr. Peregrinus and then sent to Ariminum. His title Propraetor as given in 27.7.11 would represent his status after the Consuls for 209 had entered office until his successor arrived." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1600> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1600" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 26.23.1 Provinces and armies 26.28." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1536> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1536" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by the Senate with instructions to the Consuls to collect the remnants of the armies of Sempronius Gracchus and Fulvius Flaccus (Liv. 25.22.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1368> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1368" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 23.30.16, cf. 24.3, and 25.2." .
